content:
Enhance Service Coverage and Boost Resource Productivity by Scheduling Across Multiple Time Zones.

Increase resource utilization and reduce response time by enabling your resources to service multiple time zones in one shift. Set operating hours on secondary service territories in various time zones to maximize resource availability.

Where: This feature is available in Lightning Experience and Salesforce Classic in Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer editions with the Field Service managed package installed.

Why: Melissa has Columbus, GA, as her primary service territory with 9:00 AM to 5:00 PM operating hours and a secondary service territory Phenix City, AL, also with 9:00 AM to 5:00 PM operating hours. Her availability is calculated from each respective territory's operating hours such that Melissa is available to work for 9 hours overall.

How: In Setup, go to Field Service Settings and verify that Enhanced Scheduling and Optimization is enabled. Define Operating Hours on secondary service territory memberships in different time zones.
title: Enhanced Scheduling Across Multiple Time Zones
